{{Glossary
|Entry=Image Frame
|Other Aliases=Image Frametic Domain
|Description=Image schemas are prelinguistic representations of highly frametic patterns arising from imagistic domains of sensory-motor experience that recur in a variety of embodied domains (e.g. containers, paths, forces, scalarity, balance, locomotion).  Image schemas, as embodied structures, have a psychological reality, are internally structured, and motivate conceptual metaphor mappings.


|Entered by=Karie
}}

